==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paroxysm
<hw>Par"ox*ysm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>paroxysme</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to sharpen, irritate;
<grk>para`</grk> beside, beyond + <?/ to sharpen, from <?/ sharp.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The fit, attack, or exacerbation, of
a disease that occurs at intervals, or has decided remissions or
intermissions.</def> <rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any sudden and violent emotion; spasmodic passion or
action; a convulsion; a fit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The returning <qex>paroxysms</qex> of diffidence and despair.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paroxysmal</ent>⟦br⟧
